SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c05050545
Version: 1

HPSBGN03560 rev.1 - HP Operations Orchestration using Java Deserialization,
Remote Arbitrary Code Execution

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2016-03-16
Last Updated: 2016-03-16

Potential Security Impact: Remote Arbitrary Code Execution

Source: Hewlett Packard Enterprise, Product Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A vulnerability in Apache Commons Collections (ACC) for handling Java object
deserialization was addressed by HP Operations Orchestration. The
vulnerability could be exploited remotely to allow remote code execution.

References:

CVE-2016-1997
PSRT110056
CERT-VU#576313

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP Operations Orchestration Software:

Operations Orchestration - v10.x prior to v10.51
Operations Orchestration content - all versions prior to v1.7.0

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2016-1997    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P)       7.5
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HPE has made the following mitigation information available to resolve the
vulnerability for the impacted version of HP Operations Orchestration:

For Operations Orchestration v10.x prior to v10.51:

Documentation link: https://softwaresupport.hp.com/group/softwaresupport/sear
ch-result/-/facetsearch/document/KM02017066?lang=en&cc=us&hpappid=202392_OSP_
PRO_HPE

Patch is available for downloaded from the following location:
http://support.openview.hp.com/selfsolve/document/LID/OO_00037

For Operations Orchestration content prior to v1.7.0:

Deploy base content pack 1.7.0 from the following location:
https://hpln.hpe.com/contentoffering/hp-oo-base-content

